# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback for the Shopify embedded app.
#
# The app uses BrowserRouter (path-based routing) because Shopify's
# <ui-nav-menu> web component navigates via path, not hash. When App
# Bridge points the embedded iframe at /products, /compose, /calendar,
# or /settings, CF Pages must serve the SPA shell (index.html) for those
# paths instead of returning 404 (or a default 308 redirect to root).
# React Router then takes over and renders the right page in-browser.
#
# Single catch-all rule. We intentionally do NOT list per-route entries:
# CF Pages's _redirects parser treats explicit lines `/products
# /index.html 200` as redirects rather than rewrites on this project,
# which 308s back to `/`. The wildcard form `/* /index.html 200` is
# applied correctly as a passthrough/rewrite — unknown path serves the
# SPA shell with the original URL preserved.
#
# Static assets in /assets/ are unaffected: Pages serves files-on-disk
# directly without consulting _redirects.
/*  /index.html  200
